ialBalance` using only native ETH, then unwraps or swaps the donated token inventory into ETH","The final `require(address(this).balance >= initialBalance + 0.1 ether)` passes even if `_sweepBounties()` produced no new proceeds"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"USDC or USDT blacklisting can permanently DoS all future recoveries","locations":["FlawVerifier.sol:55","FlawVerifier.sol:56","FlawVerifier.sol:96","FlawVerifier.sol:103"],"claim":"The contract must successfully swap any positive USDC or USDT balance through Uniswap, but it has no skip path, rescue path, or per-token isolation if those centralized stablecoins refuse transfers. If this contract is ever blacklisted or transfer-blocked by USDC or USDT while holding a positive balance, `_swapTokenToEth()` reverts and aborts the entire `executeOnOpportunity()` transaction.","impact":"A single blocked USDC or USDT balance prevents liquidation of every other recovered asset as well, because the whole recovery transaction reverts before completion. Since the contract has no token rescue mechanism, subsequent bounty proceeds can remain stranded behind one centralized-token failure mode indefinitely.","paths":["`_sweepBounties()` or a direct transfer leaves a positive USDC or USDT balance in `FlawVerifier`","The token issuer blacklists this contract or otherwise causes transfers from it to fail","A later `executeOnOpportunity()` call reaches `_swapTokenToEth(USDC)` or `_swapTokenToEth(USDT)`","The router transfer fails and the full recovery transaction reverts, blocking liquidation of all assets"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[]}
